<Content>nice place to stay at outskirt of town after reading all the negative reviews, I was afraid it's gonna be a real dump. However, given most of our time will be spent driving out of san juan, the location of this hotel seems to make sense compared to something in OSJ or condado and the price seems much lower to comparable places. We took a risk and we found the place sufficient for our need. rooms are clean, lobby is barren but the clean, white fluorescent lighting seems refreshing compared to other yellowish moody woody lobbies. A/C is quiet and cold. The hotel is surely nothing fancy but we don't care for that. the construction thing going on next door is not an issue at all. best thing of all is its proximity to highways going out to other parts of PR and you don't have to fight the traffic thru OSJ or condado every day and night. If I go back to SJ, I will not hesitate to stay there again. I would have give it a 3-star but given the many bad reviews here which I don't think really reflect the state the hotel is in, I am giving a 4 to counterbalance a little bit. 
