<Content>Over 25 years My family and I stay at this hotel each time we visit PR for one or two nights before heading into the island. We have been staying there for over twenty five years. We have stayed at several other hotels in San Juan - El Convento, Hilton and etc. but always go back to Excelsior. The accomodations have changed with time ( the kitchenette suites are smaller and you can't cook in the room anymore), but the main features have stayed the same. The rooms are large, comfortable and clean. The staff is unobtrusive, but helpful when needed. The restaurants are ok if you don't want to leave the premises, but we prefer to find restaurants with local flavor. The hotel is located in a mixed business and residential area. They have on site parking and nearby bus service. The view of the laguna from the higher floors is stunning. We highly recommend the Excelsior to anyone who doesn't want to stay at a touristy type place and desires convenience, peace and quiet. 
