<Content>Absolutely NOTHING wrong with this hotel At the time we stayed there, the hotel was undergoing renovations; however we found the lobby decor (the remodeled part) quite pleasing, had very good service from the desk staff at check-in and they also helped us find our way around a little bit. Two restaurants on site, both quite good. The room was comfortable - neither dirty nor immaculate. The neighborhood is fair, but you'll certainly find other hotels in more touristy areas. The bus to Old San Juan runs right in front of the hotel, it's only a few quarters and a few minutes away to OSJ.Met many people on our cruise who stayed in San Juan prior to our embarkation, and NOBODY had a better experience than we had, even for MUCH MUCH more money. I heard complaints on everything ranging from noise to comfort to towel size to price. But I can honestly say that the only disappointment that I had at the Hotel Excelsior was the fact that the renovation closed the main elevator, and the only ride up and down was a rickety service elevator. But other than that inconvenience, I would have no problem staying there again. It's not the Ritz, but it's not the pits. :) 
