<Author>queenofeverything
<Content>So its not the ritz but its clean and friendly We needed a hotel for one nite before our cruise. After reading the many reviews I was reluctant but at the last minute decided to book this hotel due to its location to the cruise ships. Its located in the downtown area of San Juan. From the airport its about 15 minutes and cost us (4 people/6 bags) $16.50 in taxi fare. From Old San Juan it is an $8.00 taxi ride for 4. We arrived in San Juan at 9pm and needed a hotel for one nite for 4 (2 adults/2children). The hotel is very old, guessing from the decor the 1950s, early 50s. They were booked but because I needed two beds they upgraded us to a suite. We had a small living room; sofa, love seat, dinnette for 2, stove, frig, ironing board, hair dryer. There was absolutely no artwork on the white walls which made it look even more blah. The bedroom was much the same with the addition of a picture over each bed. There is a color TV with all the channels and gaming system for the kids. Our view was that of the building being built next door although we didn't hear any of the construction going on. But again, view didn't matter to us. The bathroom shows the age of the place as it is layers of paint which are cracked and could be picked off, especially by little hands. The toliet is what surprised me as it is one you would find in a public gas station, no tank/lid, etc. Now that I've shared all that I rated this place average even though it is old and dated because it was very clean, had a good restaurant and the staff were very friendly and helpful. The old addage: don't judge a book by its cover certainly applies here. I have seen some big named hotel chains here in the states who are on the expensive side who are not as clean as this place. The air conditioner also works very well too, and no musty smells either. We had breakfast in the parsian cafe downstairs and it was good. You have your choice from I believe 4 items for $6.90. Its more than the local denny's but not as expensive as I was led to believe by reading previous reviews. The service was great, very friendly and quick. As was the hotel staff. Upon check-in we were checked right in and in our room within 10 minutes tops. At check out it was just as good and they made arrangements for a larger taxi as we had 6 large bags, carry ons and of course our children. If you need a CLEAN place to lay your head for a quick overnite its not a bad place to stay. 
