<Content>Good hotel for "budget" travel We stayed here for one night before leaving the Island. Used Priceline and ended up here for $95. We arrived at 3 and had to wait by the pool for an hour for our room to be cleaned. But the room was fine - tile floor, 2 small beds, a little kitchen in the closet, working TV with cable, and a table with chairs. We asked for a crib and it came right away. The restaurant downstairs is expensive but 2 blocks away is a good local place, full breakfast for under $3. There is also a nearby market where you could get food to stock your fridge with. The hotel is right on the bus route of 3 buses that will take you into the old city in 5 minutes for a quarter. We took buses both ways and were quite pleased. There were also plenty of taxis for our ride to the airport. Overall I was concerned when Priceline booked this hotel, however it was fine - nothing fancy, but much cheaper than other hotels and clean. 
