<Content>"Piece of crap" might be rather harsh, Brooklyn! We booked accommodation at the last minute, and for a very busy long weekend (MLK, San Sebastian festival). So with very few options available, we tried Hotel Excelsior. The $120/nt rate was not too bad (could have been worse). Admittedly, our first night was a rip off. Our flight was late and we didn't arrive until 2:30 a.m. Looking forward to a good nights' sleep, we were very disappointed to be placed in the most basic of rooms with a double bed (I had specifically requested a King), sheer curtains, no carpet on the floor, and MDF/student dorm-style furniture. However, after we expressed our disappointment, the staff arranged another room for the rest of our stay and we we were quite satisfied with it. Staff: Quite friendly Food: The hotel has a small cafe that serves breakfast and lunch. Food is okay. Wait staff is friendly (although slow service in the a.m. indicates they need more of them). Could definitely use a bigger coffee maker (long waits for them to brew new pots!) Pool: Small, clean with lounge chairs. Can sit on the bistro patio and look out over it. The hours are only 9:00 to 6:00, which is disappointing if you like to swim early or late. Summary: As one other reviewer put it, the Excelsior is not the Ritz, so if you're expecting that, go elsewhere. But if you're like us, and just want a relatively clean, reasonable, friendly place to lie your head at night, then I'd recommend giving it a go. 
